 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-INV-003: Index synchronization depends on programmer discipline — no compile-time enforcement. PROBLEM: Five secondary indexes (entity_index, attribute_index, vaet_index, avet_index, live_view) plus MaterializedViews are maintained by index_datom(), which must be called for every datom inserted into the primary BTreeSet. Four insertion paths exist: (1) genesis() calls views.observe_datom() NOT index_datom(), rebuilds indexes in from_datoms(). (2) from_datoms() calls views.observe_datom() directly, rebuilds indexes separately. (3) apply_tx() calls index_datom() per datom. (4) apply_datoms() rebuilds everything from scratch. Paths 1 and 2 bypass index_datom(), meaning MaterializedViews updates and index updates are separate code paths. JUSTIFICATION: The single-writer principle demands exactly one function maintains derived state. Multiple paths implementing the same derivation violate DRY and create silent divergence risk. The correct architecture: index_datom() is the sole function updating BOTH indexes AND MaterializedViews. All insertion paths call it. SOLUTION: Unify insertion paths — make index_datom() call observe_datom() internally. Remove all direct observe_datom() calls outside index_datom(). VERIFICATION: grep -n 'observe_datom' store.rs returns only the definition and calls from index_datom. DEPENDENCIES: Prerequisite for F-TYPE-001 (once paths unified, isomorphism proptest becomes meaningful). Interacts with F-PERF-001 (merge rebuild) — unified path enables incremental merge. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs:943,1016-1018,1085-1095,1165. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 0. EFFORT: 4h."
